{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "ClientSide Ecommerce API",
    "description": "Storefront API (2026-04): health, auth, Google OAuth2, JWT exchange, profile, service area, catalog.\n\n**Setup**\n- `npm run dev` â€” default **4100**. `npm run db:migrate`. A **shop** row must exist; set **`shopId`** (collection or environment variable).\n- **`.env`:** `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `API_PUBLIC_URL`, Google OAuth vars. Redirect URI in Google Console: `{API_PUBLIC_URL}/api/oauth/callback/google`.\n\n**JWT**\n- Login/register/oauth/jwt return **`accessToken`**. Protected routes: `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}`.\n\n**Postman + OAuth JWT exchange**\n- **Cookie flow:** After Google opens `/api/oauth/callback/google`, the **`storefront_oauth_exchange`** cookie is set on the API host. Postmanâ€™s cookie jar often **does not** get that cookie unless you use the Postman **Interceptor** or paste it manually.\n- **`POST /api/auth/oauth/jwt`** with body **`{}`** when the valid cookie is sent.\n- **Dev email mint:** body `{\"email\":\"â€¦\"}` only if **`ALLOW_EMAIL_ONLY_JWT_EXCHANGE=true`** (never production). If you get **401** with email, clear **Cookies** for `localhost:4100` â€” a **stale** `storefront_oauth_exchange` blocks the email path unless the server falls through (recent fix).\n\n**CORS**\n- API allows credentials for **`CORS_ORIGIN`** (e.g. `http://localhost:5173`). OAuth `POST /api/oauth/sign-in/social` may need **`Origin`** matching that value when testing from CLI.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:4100" },
    { "key": "shopId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "buyer@example.com" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "secret12" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "corsOrigin", "value": "http://localhost:5173" }
  ],
